Welcome to FuzzyYellowBalls.com's Youtube channel!  We teach tennis on the internet using video.  Our video tennis lessons are distinct because we use a greenscreen -- the thing the weatherman stands in front of.  But instead of the weather we've got someone hitting a tennis ball! description:
Molon labe (mo-lone lah-veh)

Two little words...

With these two words, two concepts were verbalized that have lived for nearly 2500 years. They characterize both the heart of the Warrior, and the indomitable spirit of mankind. From the ancient Greek, they are the reply of the Spartan General-King Leonidas to Xerxes, the Persian Emperor who came with 600,000 of the fiercest fighting troops in the world to conquer little Greece, and the birthplace of civilization as we know it. 

When Xerxes offered to spare the lives of Leonidas, his 300 personal bodyguards and a handful of Thebans and others who volunteered to defend their country, if they would lay down their weapons, Leonidas shouted: Molon labe!

They mean, "Come and get them!" They live on today as the most notable quote in military history. And so began the classic example of courage and valor in its dismissal of overwhelming superiority of numbers, wherein the heart and spirit of brave men overcame insuperable odds.

description:
Emilio Santoyo (Mexico, 1990) is an independent filmmaker with a bachelor's degree on Film Directing at CENTRO (Mexico City). He is a Berlinale Talents (Guadalajara) alumnus and currently develops his Master of Film Research at the Netherlands Film Academy with the support of the CONACYT- SACPC (AFPE). His work investigates themes such as the ethics behind filmmaking and representation, family, and memory, questioning and expanding the possibilities of fiction in cinema through non-hierarchical and non-industrial methods of production. 

Besides his work as a producer, he directed the short film “The perfect absent” (2019), as well as the fictional feature-length films “Ana’s desire” (2019) and “This savage beast” (2023). His films have won several international awards and been selected in more than 50 film festivals such as Mostra - Sao Paulo, Habana, Zaragoza, Singapore, Morelia, Los Cabos, Cinequest, Lugo Film

description: This channel is more or less dedicated to free flight model gliders, both catapult launched gliders (CLG) and hand launched gliders (HLG), also known as tip launched gliders (TLG).  My hope is  to share videos that help others learn about this wonderfully rewarding hobby/sport.  In some cases I have used slow motion photography to capture gliders in flight or being launched.  Free flight gliders can be flown indoors or outdoors.  Indoor models are challenging because they must be built for maximum duration in still air, while outdoor gliders are designed to catch thermals and stay aloft for several minutes riding columns or rising air, just like hawks and eagles.

Ciao e benvenuti nel nostro canale YouTube! Siamo online dal 2006 e sin dal primo giorno, la nostra passione ci ha guidato nella creazione dei contenuti. Nel corso degli anni, abbiamo trattato una varietà di temi, tra cui tutorial, intrattenimento, viaggi e vlog. Siamo stati anche tra i primi al mondo a introdurre l'ASMR e i video di rumore bianco. Negli ultimi anni, abbiamo continuato a studiare e sperimentare le frequenze e le possibili applicazioni di questi suoni.

Tu, con i tuoi commenti e le tue esperienze, sei una parte fondamentale di questa ricerca. Ti invitiamo a sentirti parte di una comunità che ricerca e sperimenta. La nostra passione risiede nel tentare e nell'interrogare.

Il tuo supporto attraverso l'iscrizione e i "mi piace" è fondamentale per il nostro impegno quotidiano. Ci sforziamo di garantire la massima qualità senza interruzioni pubblicitarie nei video, in linea con la nostra etica e rispetto per la fiducia che ci hai accordato.

description:
Welcome to Duke Video, the place to be for awesome Powersports action videos! Featuring epic clips from Formula 1, Isle of Man TT, Road Racing, MotoGP, Motocross, Rallying, WRC, BTCC, Le Mans and many more forms of motorsport.  

Whether you're into retro archive clips of the 1960s or the latest motorsport and powersport clip from championships around the world, Duke Video offers the perfect remedy for every petrolheads craving!
